translated: Enander, Einar, Captain, Fire Chief, Jönköping, b. November 20, 1886 in Gothenburg to Axel Wilhelm E. and Hilda Elisabeth Bohle. Married in 1934 to Lola Eiding. Children: Gunhild b. 1916 (from a previous marriage). Education: graduated from high school in 1906, commissioned officer in 1908, completed fire officer training with the Gothenburg Fire Department from 1910-1912, completed a gym instructor course in 1910, studied building construction in 1920, and completed various specialized courses in firefighting and civilian defense services. Studied with the Berlin and Copenhagen Fire Departments in 1912 and went on educational trips to Germany, Holland, England, France, Finland, and Denmark. Was the substitute gymnasium teacher at Gothenburg's upper secondary school from 1910-1912, substitute fire lieutenant with the Norrköping Fire Department in 1911, held various appointments as fire chief with the Gothenburg Fire Department from 1914-1917 and as acting fire chief in Örebro in 1916. Was editor of the Fire Service Journal from 1916-1920, head of the fire department at the Ludwigshergs Works AB in Stockholm from 1913-1916, head of the Gothenburg Fire Department from 1918-1921, and has been the fire chief of Jönköping since 1921 and of Huskvarna since 1943. Is a member of the Swedish Fire Protection Association Board, chairman of the Jönköping City Work Society, and a member and secretary of several firefighting and aviation commissions and organizations. Is a consultant for government and private sector authorities, gives lectures, and is a leader of training courses. Has written various brochures about firefighting. Hobbies include driving (racing), skiing. Has been awarded RVO, RODO, and the Finnish Fire Brigade Association's Honorary Badge, and has been granted life membership in A-B General Insurance Brands and Städ. Allm. BrandstodisiboL GM and Abo Fri Fire Department MM and Finnish medical for humanitarian activities.
